<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>Meritor/WABCO Hydraulic ABS for Medium-Duty Trucks, Buses and Motor Home Chassis - TROUBLESHOOTING AND
        TESTING - SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS AND COMPONENT TESTS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="test" graphiccount="0">
        <title>SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS AND COMPONENT TESTS</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Tire Size Range</title>
            <para>For proper hydraulic ABS operation, front and rear tire sizes must be within 16% of each other.</para>
            <para>Contact the Meritor WABCO Customer Support Center at 800-535-5560 if you plan a tire size difference
                greater than &#177;8%.
            </para>
            <para>Calculate the tire size with the following equation:</para>
            <table id="tmm39-4" frame="none" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                <tgroup cols="3" colsep="0" rowsep="0" align="center">
                    <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1" align="center" colwidth="1.25 in" colsep="1" rowsep="0"/>
                    <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2" align="center" colwidth="0.85in" colsep="1"/>
                    <colspec colnum="3" colname="col3" align="left" colwidth=".75 in" colsep="1" rowsep="0"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>% Difference =</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="underscr">RPM Steer</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>RPM Drive</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>- 1 x 100</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>RPM = tire revolutions per mile</para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>When troubleshooting or testing the ABS system, do not damage the connector terminals.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Voltage Check</title>
            <para>Voltage must be between 9.5 and 14 volts for the 12-volt hydraulic ABS to function properly.</para>
            <para>Check voltage as follows:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn ignition ON.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check for proper voltage:</para>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">Cab-mounted ECU:</emph>
                    Pins 12 and 1 and 12 and 2 on the 18-pin connector.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">Frame-mounted ECU:</emph>
                    Pins 9 and 3 and 9 and 2 on the black connector.
                </para>
                <para>If voltage is not between 9.5 and 14 volts, verify proper wiring connections. Make corrections as
                    required.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
